Learn instead of unemployed: Pilot project for unskilled in tourism
On the lakes of Mecklenburg today will launch a pilot project for the tourism industry.
Under the leadership of the Federal Labour Agency to 49 men and women who are already qualified as an unskilled work, across three winter to professionals in the industry for hotels and restaurants.
"What is new is that the six-month courses end with qualifications," said Carmen Wiechert from work Neubrandenburg agency.
The benefits would be many: The participants will not unemployed, the companies would trained professionals who increasingly missing in hotels and restaurants, and the agency should not finance unemployment.
In the project, the Chamber of Commerce and Industry in Neubrandenburg, as well as the German hotel and restaurant association (soucheff) are also involved in Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania.
